# train_and_save.py
import pandas as pd
import joblib
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OrdinalEncoder
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import (
    classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve
)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

try:
    from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
    has_imblearn = True
except Exception:
    has_imblearn = False

# --- CONFIG ---
LABEL_MAP = {"good": 0, "bad": 1}   # explicit mapping: 1 = bad
RANDOM_STATE = 42

# --- Load your dataframes ---
bad_df = df1.copy()
good_df = df2.copy()
df = pd.concat([good_df, bad_df], ignore_index=True)

# --- Ensure raw class mapped to numeric ---
if df['class'].dtype == object:
    df['class'] = df['class'].map(LABEL_MAP)
else:
    df['class'] = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Feature Engineering
# =====================

# --- Feature Engineering (no path) ---
df['body'] = df.get('body', "").fillna("")
df['body_length'] = df['body'].apply(len)
df = df.drop(columns=['body', 'path'], errors="ignore")   # <-- DROP path completely

# Define columns
cat_cols = ['method']
num_cols = [
    'single_q', 'double_q', 'dashes', 'braces', 'spaces',
    'percentages', 'semicolons', 'angle_brackets', 'special_chars',
    'body_length', 'badwords_count'
]

# Ensure numeric cols exist
for c in num_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = 0
    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c].fillna(0), errors='coerce').fillna(0.0)

# Ensure categorical cols exist
for c in cat_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = "missing"
    df[c] = df[c].fillna("missing").astype(str)


# Final X, y
X = df[cat_cols + num_cols]
y = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Train / Test split
# =====================
X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
)

# --- Encode categorical ---
ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1)
ord_enc.fit(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_train_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_test_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_test_raw[cat_cols])

cat_enc_names = [f"{c}_enc" for c in cat_cols]
X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_train_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_train_raw.index)
X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_test_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_test_raw.index)

X_train_comb = pd.concat([X_train_enc.reset_index(drop=True), X_train_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
X_test_comb  = pd.concat([X_test_enc.reset_index(drop=True),  X_test_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

# --- Oversample training set ---
if has_imblearn:
    ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
else:
    from sklearn.utils import resample
    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
                                  replace=True,
                                  n_samples=len(majority),
                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)

]

    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
else:
    from sklearn.utils import resample
    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
                                  replace=True,
                                  n_samples=len(majority),
                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)
    y_train_bal = train_balanced_df['class']
    X_train_bal = train_balanced_df.drop(columns=['class'])

# Scaling
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaler.fit(X_train_bal)
X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train_bal)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_comb)
scaler_feature_names = X_train_bal.columns.tolist()

# =====================
# Fine-tuning
# =====================
param_grids = {
    "svm": {
        "C": [0.1, 1, 10],
        "gamma": ["scale", 0.01, 0.001],
        "kernel": ["rbf", "poly"]
    },
    "random_forest": {
        "n_estimators": [100, 200, 500],
        "max_depth": [None, 10, 20, 30],
        "min_samples_split": [2, 5, 10]
    },
    "knn": {
        "n_neighbors": [3, 5, 7, 9],
        "weights": ["uniform", "distance"],
        "p": [1, 2]  # Manhattan vs Euclidean
    }
}

base_models = {
    "svm": SVC(probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "random_forest": RandomForestClassifier(random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "knn": KNeighborsClassifier()
}

best_models = {}

for name, model in base_models.items():
    print(f"\n=== Tuning {name.upper()} ===")
    gs = GridSearchCV(
        estimator=model,
        param_grid=param_grids[name],
        cv=CV,
        scoring="roc_auc",
        n_jobs=-1,
        verbose=1
    )
    gs.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    best_models[name] = gs.best_estimator_
    print(f"Best params for {name}: {gs.best_params_}")

    # Evaluate
    y_pred = gs.predict(X_test_scaled)
    print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Good','Bad']))
    

    if hasattr(gs, "predict_proba"):
        y_proba = gs.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba)
        print("ROC AUC:", auc)

# =====================
# Save artifacts
# =====================
joblib.dump(ord_enc, 'ordinal_encoder.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler, 'scaler.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler_feature_names, 'feature_columns.pkl')
joblib.dump(LABEL_MAP, 'label_map.pkl')

for name, model in best_models.items():
    joblib.dump(model, f"{name}_model.pkl")
    print(f"Saved fine-tuned model: {name}_model.pkl")

# train_and_save.py
import pandas as pd
import joblib
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OrdinalEncoder
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import (
    classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve
)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

try:
    from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
    has_imblearn = True
except Exception:
    has_imblearn = False

# --- CONFIG ---
LABEL_MAP = {"good": 0, "bad": 1}   # explicit mapping: 1 = bad
RANDOM_STATE = 42

# --- Load your dataframes ---
bad_df = df1.copy()
good_df = df2.copy()
df = pd.concat([good_df, bad_df], ignore_index=True)

# --- Ensure raw class mapped to numeric ---
if df['class'].dtype == object:
    df['class'] = df['class'].map(LABEL_MAP)
else:
    df['class'] = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Feature Engineering
# =====================

# --- Feature Engineering (no path) ---
df['body'] = df.get('body', "").fillna("")
df['body_length'] = df['body'].apply(len)
df = df.drop(columns=['body', 'path'], errors="ignore")   # <-- DROP path completely

# Define columns
cat_cols = ['method']
num_cols = [
    'single_q', 'double_q', 'dashes', 'braces', 'spaces',
    'percentages', 'semicolons', 'angle_brackets', 'special_chars',
    'body_length', 'badwords_count'
]

# Ensure numeric cols exist
for c in num_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = 0
    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c].fillna(0), errors='coerce').fillna(0.0)

# Ensure categorical cols exist
for c in cat_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = "missing"
    df[c] = df[c].fillna("missing").astype(str)


# Final X, y
X = df[cat_cols + num_cols]
y = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Train / Test split
# =====================
X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
)

# --- Encode categorical ---
ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1)
ord_enc.fit(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_train_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_test_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_test_raw[cat_cols])

cat_enc_names = [f"{c}_enc" for c in cat_cols]
X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_train_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_train_raw.index)
X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_test_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_test_raw.index)

X_train_comb = pd.concat([X_train_enc.reset_index(drop=True), X_train_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
X_test_comb  = pd.concat([X_test_enc.reset_index(drop=True),  X_test_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

# --- Oversample training set ---
if has_imblearn:
    ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
else:
    from sklearn.utils import resample
    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
                                  replace=True,
                                  n_samples=len(majority),
                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)
    y_train_bal = train_balanced_df['class']
    X_train_bal = train_balanced_df.drop(columns=['class'])

# --- Scaling ---
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaler.fit(X_train_bal)
X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train_bal)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_comb)

scaler_feature_names = X_train_bal.columns.tolist()

# --- Models ---
models = {
    "svm": SVC(kernel="rbf", probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "random_forest": RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "knn": KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)
}

metrics_summary = []

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
for name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
    y_pred_train = model.predict(X_train_scaled)  # Get predictions on the training data for accuracy
    print(f"\n=== {name} ===")
    print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Good', 'Bad']))
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_train) # Use predictions on training data and balanced training labels
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    print(f"Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"Test Accuracy:  {test_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"Overfitting Gap: {train_accuracy - test_accuracy:.4f}")

    # Confusion matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Good','Bad'], yticklabels=['Good','Bad'])
    plt.title(f"{name} - Confusion Matrix")
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Actual")
    plt.show()

    # AUC
    if hasattr(model, "predict_proba"):
        y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba)
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"{name} (AUC={auc:.3f})")
    else:
        auc = None

    metrics_summary.append({
        "model": name,
        "accuracy": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
        "auc": auc
    })


# ROC curves
if any(m['auc'] is not None for m in metrics_summary):
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    plt.xlabel("FPR"); plt.ylabel("TPR"); plt.title("ROC Curves"); plt.legend(); plt.show()

# --- Save artifacts ---
joblib.dump(ord_enc, 'ordinal_encoder.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler, 'scaler.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler_feature_names, 'feature_columns.pkl')
joblib.dump(LABEL_MAP, 'label_map.pkl')

for name, model in models.items():
    joblib.dump(model, f"{name}_model.pkl")
    print(f"Saved model: {name}_model.pkl")

print("Saved preprocessing artifacts: ordinal_encoder.pkl, scaler.pkl, feature_columns.pkl, label_map.pkl")

import pandas as pd
import joblib
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OrdinalEncoder
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import (
    classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve
)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

try:
    from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
    has_imblearn = True
except Exception:
    has_imblearn = False

# --- CONFIG ---
LABEL_MAP = {"good": 0, "bad": 1}   # explicit mapping: 1 = bad
RANDOM_STATE = 42

# --- Load your dataframes ---
bad_df = df1.copy()
good_df = df2.copy()
df = pd.concat([good_df, bad_df], ignore_index=True)

# --- Ensure raw class mapped to numeric ---
if df['class'].dtype == object:
    df['class'] = df['class'].map(LABEL_MAP)
else:
    df['class'] = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Feature Engineering
# =====================

# --- Feature Engineering (no path) ---
df['body'] = df.get('body', "").fillna("")
df['body_length'] = df['body'].apply(len)
df = df.drop(columns=['body', 'path'], errors="ignore")   # <-- DROP path completely

# Define columns
cat_cols = ['method']
num_cols = [
    'single_q', 'double_q', 'dashes', 'braces', 'spaces',
    'percentages', 'semicolons', 'angle_brackets', 'special_chars',
    'body_length', 'badwords_count'
]

# Ensure numeric cols exist
for c in num_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = 0
    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c].fillna(0), errors='coerce').fillna(0.0)

# Ensure categorical cols exist
for c in cat_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = "missing"
    df[c] = df[c].fillna("missing").astype(str)


# Final X, y
X = df[cat_cols + num_cols]
y = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Train / Test split
# =====================
X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
)

# --- Encode categorical ---
ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1)
ord_enc.fit(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_train_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_test_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_test_raw[cat_cols])

cat_enc_names = [f"{c}_enc" for c in cat_cols]
X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_train_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_train_raw.index)
X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_test_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_test_raw.index)

X_train_comb = pd.concat([X_train_enc.reset_index(drop=True), X_train_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
X_test_comb  = pd.concat([X_test_enc.reset_index(drop=True),  X_test_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

# --- Oversample training set ---
if has_imblearn:
    ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
else:
    from sklearn.utils import resample
    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
                                  replace=True,
                                  n_samples=len(majority),
                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)
    y_train_bal = train_balanced_df['class']
    X_train_bal = train_balanced_df.drop(columns=['class'])

# --- Scaling ---
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaler.fit(X_train_bal)
X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train_bal)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_comb)

scaler_feature_names = X_train_bal.columns.tolist()

# --- Models ---
models = {
    "svm": SVC(kernel="rbf", probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "random_forest": RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "knn": KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)
}

metrics_summary = []

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
for name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
    y_pred_train = model.predict(X_train_scaled)  # Get predictions on the training data for accuracy
    print(f"\n=== {name} ===")
    print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Good', 'Bad']))
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_train) # Use predictions on training data and balanced training labels
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    print(f"Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"Test Accuracy:  {test_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"Overfitting Gap: {train_accuracy - test_accuracy:.4f}")

    # Confusion matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Good','Bad'], yticklabels=['Good','Bad'])
    plt.title(f"{name} - Confusion Matrix")
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Actual")
    plt.show()

    # AUC
    if hasattr(model, "predict_proba"):
        y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba)
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"{name} (AUC={auc:.3f})")
    else:
        auc = None

    metrics_summary.append({
        "model": name,
        "accuracy": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
        "auc": auc
    })


# ROC curves
if any(m['auc'] is not None for m in metrics_summary):
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    plt.xlabel("FPR"); plt.ylabel("TPR"); plt.title("ROC Curves"); plt.legend(); plt.show()

# --- Save artifacts ---
joblib.dump(ord_enc, 'ordinal_encoder.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler, 'scaler.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler_feature_names, 'feature_columns.pkl')
joblib.dump(LABEL_MAP, 'label_map.pkl')

for name, model in models.items():
    joblib.dump(model, f"{name}_model.pkl")
    print(f"Saved model: {name}_model.pkl")

print("Saved preprocessing artifacts: ordinal_encoder.pkl, scaler.pkl, feature_columns.pkl, label_map.pkl")

","import pandas as pd
","import joblib
","import numpy as np
","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
","from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OrdinalEncoder
","from sklearn.svm import SVC
","from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
","from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
","from sklearn.metrics import (
","    classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve
",")
","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
","import seaborn as sns
","
","try:
","    from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
","    has_imblearn = True
","except Exception:
","    has_imblearn = False
","
","# --- CONFIG ---
","LABEL_MAP = {"good": 0, "bad": 1}   # explicit mapping: 1 = bad
","RANDOM_STATE = 42
","
","# --- Load your dataframes ---
","bad_df = df1.copy()
","good_df = df2.copy()
","df = pd.concat([good_df, bad_df], ignore_index=True)
","
","# --- Ensure raw class mapped to numeric ---
","if df['class'].dtype == object:
","    df['class'] = df['class'].map(LABEL_MAP)
","else:
","    df['class'] = df['class'].astype(int)
","
","# =====================
","# Feature Engineering
","# =====================
","
","# --- Feature Engineering (no path) ---
","df['body'] = df.get('body', "").fillna("")
","df['body_length'] = df['body'].apply(len)
","df = df.drop(columns=['body', 'path'], errors="ignore")   # <-- DROP path completely
","
","# Define columns
","cat_cols = ['method']
","num_cols = [
","    'single_q', 'double_q', 'dashes', 'braces', 'spaces',
","    'percentages', 'semicolons', 'angle_brackets', 'special_chars',
","    'body_length', 'badwords_count'
","]
","
","# Ensure numeric cols exist
","for c in num_cols:
","    if c not in df.columns:
","        df[c] = 0
","    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c].fillna(0), errors='coerce').fillna(0.0)
","
","# Ensure categorical cols exist
","for c in cat_cols:
","    if c not in df.columns:
","        df[c] = "missing"
","    df[c] = df[c].fillna("missing").astype(str)
","
","
","# Final X, y
","X = df[cat_cols + num_cols]
","y = df['class'].astype(int)
","
","# =====================
","# Train / Test split
","# =====================
","X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
","    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
",")
","
","# --- Encode categorical ---
","ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1)
","ord_enc.fit(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
","X_train_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
","X_test_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_test_raw[cat_cols])
","
","cat_enc_names = [f"{c}_enc" for c in cat_cols]
","X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_train_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_train_raw.index)
","X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_test_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_test_raw.index)
","
","X_train_comb = pd.concat([X_train_enc.reset_index(drop=True), X_train_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","X_test_comb  = pd.concat([X_test_enc.reset_index(drop=True),  X_test_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","
","# --- Oversample training set ---
","if has_imblearn:
","    ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
","    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
","else:
","    from sklearn.utils import resample
","    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
","    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
","    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
","                                  replace=True,
","                                  n_samples=len(majority),
","                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
","    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)
","    y_train_bal = train_balanced_df['class']
","    X_train_bal = train_balanced_df.drop(columns=['class'])
","
","# --- Scaling ---
","scaler = StandardScaler()
","scaler.fit(X_train_bal)
","X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train_bal)
","X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_comb)
","
","scaler_feature_names = X_train_bal.columns.tolist()
","
","# --- Models ---
","models = {
","    "svm": SVC(kernel="rbf", probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
","    "random_forest": RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
","    "knn": KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)
","}
","
","metrics_summary = []
","
","plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
","for name, model in models.items():
","    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
","    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
","    y_pred_train = model.predict(X_train_scaled)  # Get predictions on the training data for accuracy
","    print(f"\n=== {name} ===")
","    print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
","    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Good', 'Bad']))
","    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_train) # Use predictions on training data and balanced training labels
","    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
","
","    print(f"Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}")
","    print(f"Test Accuracy:  {test_accuracy:.4f}")
","    print(f"Overfitting Gap: {train_accuracy - test_accuracy:.4f}")
","
","    # Confusion matrix
","    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
","    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Good','Bad'], yticklabels=['Good','Bad'])
","    plt.title(f"{name} - Confusion Matrix")
","    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
","    plt.ylabel("Actual")
","    plt.show()
","
","    # AUC
","    if hasattr(model, "predict_proba"):
","        y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]
","        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba)
","        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
","        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"{name} (AUC={auc:.3f})")
","    else:
","        auc = None
","
","    metrics_summary.append({
","        "model": name,
","        "accuracy": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
","        "auc": auc
","    })
","
","
","# ROC curves
","if any(m['auc'] is not None for m in metrics_summary):
","    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
","    plt.xlabel("FPR"); plt.ylabel("TPR"); plt.title("ROC Curves"); plt.legend(); plt.show()
","
","# --- Save artifacts ---
","joblib.dump(ord_enc, 'ordinal_encoder.pkl')

","

","

import pandas as pd
import joblib
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OrdinalEncoder
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import (
    classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve
)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

try:
    from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
    has_imblearn = True
except Exception:
    has_imblearn = False

# --- CONFIG ---
LABEL_MAP = {"good": 0, "bad": 1}   # explicit mapping: 1 = bad
RANDOM_STATE = 42

# --- Load your dataframes ---
bad_df = df1.copy()
good_df = df2.copy()
df = pd.concat([good_df, bad_df], ignore_index=True)

# --- Ensure raw class mapped to numeric ---
if df['class'].dtype == object:
    df['class'] = df['class'].map(LABEL_MAP)
else:
    df['class'] = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Feature Engineering
# =====================

# --- Feature Engineering (no path) ---
df['body'] = df.get('body', "").fillna("")
df['body_length'] = df['body'].apply(len)
df = df.drop(columns=['body', 'path'], errors="ignore")   # <-- DROP path completely

# Define columns
cat_cols = ['method']
num_cols = [
    'single_q', 'double_q', 'dashes', 'braces', 'spaces',
    'percentages', 'semicolons', 'angle_brackets', 'special_chars',
    'body_length', 'badwords_count'
]

# Ensure numeric cols exist
for c in num_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = 0
    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c].fillna(0), errors='coerce').fillna(0.0)

# Ensure categorical cols exist
for c in cat_cols:
    if c not in df.columns:
        df[c] = "missing"
    df[c] = df[c].fillna("missing").astype(str)


# Final X, y
X = df[cat_cols + num_cols]
y = df['class'].astype(int)

# =====================
# Train / Test split
# =====================
X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
)

# --- Encode categorical ---
ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1)
ord_enc.fit(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_train_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
X_test_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_test_raw[cat_cols])

cat_enc_names = [f"{c}_enc" for c in cat_cols]
X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_train_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_train_raw.index)
X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_test_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_test_raw.index)

X_train_comb = pd.concat([X_train_enc.reset_index(drop=True), X_train_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
X_test_comb  = pd.concat([X_test_enc.reset_index(drop=True),  X_test_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

# --- Oversample training set ---
if has_imblearn:
    ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
else:
    from sklearn.utils import resample
    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
                                  replace=True,
                                  n_samples=len(majority),
                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)
    y_train_bal = train_balanced_df['class']
    X_train_bal = train_balanced_df.drop(columns=['class'])

# --- Scaling ---
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaler.fit(X_train_bal)
X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train_bal)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_comb)

scaler_feature_names = X_train_bal.columns.tolist()

# --- Models ---
models = {
    "svm": SVC(kernel="rbf", probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "random_forest": RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
    "knn": KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)
}

metrics_summary = []

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
for name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
    y_pred_train = model.predict(X_train_scaled)  # Get predictions on the training data for accuracy
    print(f"\n=== {name} ===")
    print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Good', 'Bad']))
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_train) # Use predictions on training data and balanced training labels
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    print(f"Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"Test Accuracy:  {test_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"Overfitting Gap: {train_accuracy - test_accuracy:.4f}")

    # Confusion matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Good','Bad'], yticklabels=['Good','Bad'])
    plt.title(f"{name} - Confusion Matrix")
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Actual")
    plt.show()

    # AUC
    if hasattr(model, "predict_proba"):
        y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba)
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"{name} (AUC={auc:.3f})")
    else:
        auc = None

    metrics_summary.append({
        "model": name,
        "accuracy": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
        "auc": auc
    })


# ROC curves
if any(m['auc'] is not None for m in metrics_summary):
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    plt.xlabel("FPR"); plt.ylabel("TPR"); plt.title("ROC Curves"); plt.legend(); plt.show()

# --- Save artifacts ---
joblib.dump(ord_enc, 'ordinal_encoder.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler, 'scaler.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler_feature_names, 'feature_columns.pkl')
joblib.dump(LABEL_MAP, 'label_map.pkl')

for name, model in models.items():
    joblib.dump(model, f"{name}_model.pkl")
    print(f"Saved model: {name}_model.pkl")

print("Saved preprocessing artifacts: ordinal_encoder.pkl, scaler.pkl, feature_columns.pkl, label_map.pkl")

","for c in num_cols:
","    if c not in df.columns:
","        df[c] = 0

","
","for c in cat_cols:
","    if c not in df.columns:
","        df[c] = "missing"
","    df[c] = df[c].fillna("missing").astype(str)
","
","X = df[cat_cols + num_cols]
","y = df['class'].astype(int)
","
","# --- Train/test split ---
","X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
","    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
",")
","
","ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1)
","ord_enc.fit(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
","
","X_train_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_train_raw[cat_cols])
","X_test_cat = ord_enc.transform(X_test_raw[cat_cols])
","
","cat_enc_names = [f"{c}_enc" for c in cat_cols]
","X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_train_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_train_raw.index)
","X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(X_test_cat, columns=cat_enc_names, index=X_test_raw.index)
","
","X_train_comb = pd.concat([X_train_enc.reset_index(drop=True), X_train_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","X_test_comb  = pd.concat([X_test_enc.reset_index(drop=True),  X_test_raw[num_cols].reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","
","# Oversample
","if has_imblearn:
","    ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
","    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = ros.fit_resample(X_train_comb, y_train.reset_index(drop=True))
","else:
","    from sklearn.utils import resample
","    train_df = pd.concat([X_train_comb.reset_index(drop=True), y_train.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","    majority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 0]
","    minority = train_df[train_df['class'] == 1]
","    minority_upsampled = resample(minority,
","                                  replace=True,
","                                  n_samples=len(majority),
","                                  random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
","    train_balanced_df = pd.concat([majority, minority_upsampled]).sample(frac=1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).reset_index(drop=True)
","    y_train_bal = train_balanced_df['class']
","    X_train_bal = train_balanced_df.drop(columns=['class'])
","
","# Scaling
","scaler = StandardScaler()
","scaler.fit(X_train_bal)
","X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train_bal)
","X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_comb)
","scaler_feature_names = X_train_bal.columns.tolist()
","
","# =====================

","param_grids = {
","    "svm": {
","        "C": [0.1, 1, 10],
","        "gamma": ["scale", 0.01, 0.001],
","        "kernel": ["rbf", "poly"]
","    },
","    "random_forest": {
","        "n_estimators": [100, 200, 500],
","        "max_depth": [None, 10, 20, 30],
","        "min_samples_split": [2, 5, 10]
","    },
","    "knn": {
","        "n_neighbors": [3, 5, 7, 9],
","        "weights": ["uniform", "distance"],
","        "p": [1, 2]  # Manhattan vs Euclidean
","    }
","}
","
","base_models = {
","    "svm": SVC(probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
","    "random_forest": RandomForestClassifier(random_state=RANDOM_STATE),
","    "knn": KNeighborsClassifier()
","}
","
","best_models = {}
","
","for name, model in base_models.items():
","    print(f"\n=== Tuning {name.upper()} ===")
","    gs = GridSearchCV(
","        estimator=model,
","        param_grid=param_grids[name],
","        cv=CV,
","        scoring="roc_auc",
","        n_jobs=-1,
","        verbose=1
","    )
","    gs.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
","    best_models[name] = gs.best_estimator_
","    print(f"Best params for {name}: {gs.best_params_}")
","
","    # Evaluate

","
","

","df3 = df3.drop(columns=["body", "path"], errors="ignore")
","
","# Handle categorical (method)
","df3["method"] = df3["method"].fillna("missing").astype(str)
","df3.loc[~df3["method"].isin(ord_enc.categories_[0]), "method"] = "missing"
","
","X_cat = ord_enc.transform(df3[["method"]])

","X3 = pd.concat([X_cat_df.reset_index(drop=True), df3.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
","

","
","# Scale
